https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/navoneel/brain-mri-images-for-brain-tumor-detection.

from this link, an extractable folder can be downloaded which contains 2 folders named 'yes' and 'no'.

'yes' folder contains MRI scans of brains with tumors and 'no' folder contains MRI scans of brains without tumors.

the code to split these images into training and testing data can be found in the jupyter notebook of this folder.
